{"article_id":"cl2O2Qt4mWjVCQUc","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Independent groups have already reported","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"spending over $ 8 million in the race .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"Cochran backers face hard choice","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"Mississippi Sen. Thad Cochran ' s national backers awakened to a wrenching decision Wednesday :","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"whether to continue pouring energy and cash into an effort","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"to rescue a six-term incumbent","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"who failed to win a majority of the vote in this week ' s primary .","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"The dilemma is agonizing on every level ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"forcing longtime Cochran allies","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"who have already spent millions","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"defending him","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"to gauge how realistic the beloved senior senator ' s chances are","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"to win a June 24 runoff .","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"Independent groups have already reported spending over $ 8 million in the Mississippi race ,","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"with more than $ 5 million going to support state Sen. Chris McDaniel , the hard-charging tea party candidate","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"who held Cochran below 50 percent of the vote .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"With 99.6 percent of precincts reporting ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"McDaniel led Cochran by just under 2,000 votes , 49.5 percent to 48.9 percent .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"Cochran enjoyed the backing of a muscular array of corporate PACs and interest groups ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"and received an extraordinary injection of late money from his Senate comrades .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"He took $ 27,000 in contributions from colleagues","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"including Sens . John McCain of Arizona , Orrin Hatch of Utah , Rob Portman of Ohio and John Boozman of Arkansas .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"The National Republican Senatorial Committee ,","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"which deployed field staff to Mississippi ahead of the primary","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"to bolster Cochran ' s operation ,","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"gave him $ 45,400 on May 20 .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"With the race all but set for a runoff vote later this month ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"Cochran ' s most loyal financial backers quickly reaffirmed their support for the senator .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"In a Senate GOP lunch after the primary , Republicans repeatedly emphasized","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"that there is an electability argument","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"to make","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"against McDaniel before June 24 .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"( \" He was a talk radio host , \"","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"one senator said . )","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"No one ,","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"including McDaniel ' s personal heroes such as Texas Sen. Ted Cruz ,","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"spoke up on the challenger ' s behalf .","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"But left unsaid by all parties Wednesday was precisely how much money Republicans might continue to pump into the race ,","depth":5},{"id":38,"text":"whether they believe","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"Cochran and his operation can sustain a three-week sprint to the next ballot","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"- and just how intensely Republicans are willing to target a challenger","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"who may end up as their nominee .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"Kansas Sen. Jerry Moran ,","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"who chairs the NRSC ,","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"said Wednesday","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"he continues to believe","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"Cochran would be a far better general election candidate than McDaniel .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"At the same time , he expressed deep reluctance","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"to go after McDaniel in the runoff .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"\" If Sen. Cochran has the Republican nomination ,","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"I think","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"it ' s just nearly -","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"it ' s just so highly likely","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"that he is reelected","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"and continues to be a senator , \"","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"Moran said .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"\" If McDaniel is the nominee ,","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"then I think","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"it ' s a much more difficult race ,","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"but we will be supportive of the efforts","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"to reelect a Republican in November . \"","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"Asked if it made sense to attack McDaniel over the next three weeks ,","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"as the NRSC did during the primary ,","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"Moran said :","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"\" It does not to me . \"","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"Moran also strongly indicated","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"it would not be his preference for the national party to shore up Cochran financially in the runoff .","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"\" It ' s always seemed to me","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"that incumbent senators ought to be able to raise the money","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"they need","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"to get reelected , \"","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"Moran said in an interview .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"\" No decision has been made about money ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"but my inclination is that this is not about NRSC money going into Mississippi . \"","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"Sen. Roger Wicker , Cochran ' s home-state colleague , gave a blunt answer to the question","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"of whether national Republicans should keep investing in Cochran :","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"\" Oh yeah . \"","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"\" I think","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"spending money effectively in the next three weeks saves millions in the general , \"","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"Wicker said .","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"Cochran ' s most powerful outside-group allies indicated","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"that they , too , would keep boosting the well-liked lawmaker .","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"A top official at the U.S. Chamber of Commerce tweeted","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"that the business lobby would \" stand by Cochran. \"","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"Henry Barbour , the Republican National Committee member","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"who leads the top super PAC","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"supporting Cochran ,","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"said in an email","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"that his group would continue to go \" all out \" in the race .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"The looming question , though , is how much money these groups intend to throw at a race","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"that many in Washington resent having been forced to spend money on at all .","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"Several top party strategists said","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"the process","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"of assessing Cochran ' s viability as a runoff candidate","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"is underway .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"CORRECTION :","depth":3},{"id":96,"text":"Corrected by :","depth":4},{"id":97,"text":"Nick Gass @ 06/04/2014 07:50 PM","depth":4},{"id":98,"text":"Correction :","depth":3},{"id":99,"text":"An earlier version of this story misstated Boozman ' s home state .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":199,"left":194,"right":198,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":194,"left":102,"right":193,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":102,"left":101,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":101,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":193,"left":135,"right":192,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":135,"left":132,"right":134,"relation":"elaboration","